               <p>JAMES LLOYD JONES I am a <rs id="t18270913-253-viclabel1424" type="occupation">draper</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-253-victim2090 t18270913-253-viclabel1424"></join>, and live at Charing-cross. On the 5th of August I was in <placeName id="t18270913-253-crimeloc1425">St. James'-park</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-253-crimeloc1425" type="placeName" value="St. James'-park"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18270913-253-crimeloc1425" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18270913-253-off1422 t18270913-253-crimeloc1425"></join> - two boys were going to fight, which caused a mob; a boy told me, a boy had taken my handkerchief - I felt and it was gone. I found the prisoner in Bertraun's charge. he pulled two handkerchiefs from his trousers; one of which was mine - I had not seen him near me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18270913-253-person2091">
                  ANGELIOUS 
                  BERTRAUN
               <interp inst="t18270913-253-person2091" type="surname" value="BERTRAUN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-253-person2091" type="given" value="ANGELIOUS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18270913-253-person2091" type="gender" value="indeterminate"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in the Park, and saw the prisoner take this handkerchief from the prosecutor; he walked round the crowd; I took him and found two handkerchiefs in his trousers - Jones claimed one.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. PHILLIPS. Q. Are you sure you saw all this? A. Yes.</p>
               <p>GUILTY. Aged 10.</p>
